article.description: Penny Taylor scored 15 of her 20 points in the second half as the Cleveland Rockers beat the New York Liberty for the second time in a week with a 67-58 win Friday night.
article.headline: Taylor's four 3-pointers get Rockers rolling
article.linkText: Taylor rolls 20 as Rockers win second in two days
article.story:
NEW YORK (AP) -- Maybe the Cleveland Rockers should play back-to-back games more often. Penny Taylor scored 15 of her 20 points in the second half as the Cleveland Rockers beat the New York Liberty for the second time in a week with a 67-58 win Friday night. Taylor, who broke out of a slump Thursday with 24 points against Sacramento, hit four 3-pointers as the Rockers won for the second night in a row. Cleveland buried the Liberty by hitting eight of 10 from beyond the arc, and Merlakia Jones scored 13 points for the Rockers, who frustrated the Liberty with tough defense and didn't show signs of fatigue. "It feels good to be .500,'' Cleveland coach Dan Hughes said. "I worry about back-to-backs, but I've got a lot of confidence in them. We've always been good in the second games. For whatever reason, this team really digs down for you.'' Tari Phillips scored 18 for the Liberty despite spraining her left ankle midway through the second half. She returned to the game and scored six points down the stretch, but missed a pair of layups with 1:08 left. Cleveland point guard Jennifer Rizzotti sprained her right ankle in the second half and did not return, but the Rockers put the game away with her on the bench. Phillips hit a pair of free throws and Becky Hammon had a layup to cut Cleveland's lead to 42-38 with 13:04 to go, but the Rockers regained their stroke from beyond the 3-point arc and the Liberty went cold. "They really broke our backs with the threes,'' New York coach Richie Adubato said. "Unfortunately we didn't get a lot of payback. We missed a lot o shots around the basket.'' Brandi McCain, in to replace Rizzotti, hit a 3-pointer to put Cleveland up 47-38, and the Liberty never again threatened. Taylor added a pair of 3-pointers to put the Rockers up 59-44, the largest lead of the game. "It was a goal to really focus in on these two games,'' said Taylor, who has a bulging disc in her back. "I was not happy with the way I was focusing, so this was a good two-day stretch.'' Game notes
The Rockers won the first game 80-69 in Cleveland. ... Vickie Johnson picked up a technical foul in the first half for hitting Andrade in the chest with a shoulder block after an offensive foul... The Liberty played without Sue Wicks, who is listed as day-to-day with a sprained right ankle.
